		<title>17Changes,Earlston</title>
		<content> 50 years ago there was a bigger       
 variety of smaller shops.             
 Trains provided transport.Not many    
 people had cars.Now we have no trains 
 and most people have cars .           
 The village has grown with new housing
 estates but the tweed mill, which used
 to employ 200-300 people, has closed  
 Two local building and road building  
 companies were major employers of     
 local labour.                         
 For entertainment, people went to the 
 cinema in Galashiels and, as a special
 treat, a trip to Berwick or Edinburgh.
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
